  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_NamingConventions> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#NamingConventions> ;
    narr:childCount "38"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "38e2139c17891b69c765f490a3a33c70af9521b0" ;
    narr:narration """This hub tracks the evolution of aswritten’s lexicon, documenting a transition from technical metaphors toward a literal, writing-centric vocabulary. The trajectory began by anchoring service tiers to [service level rather than org size](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ProfessionalOverEnterprise) and establishing [naming constraints](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_NamingConstraints) that prioritize 'whole perspective' over 'data package.' Subsequent shifts replaced obscure or metaphorical terms: [distillation became perspective creation](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DistillationToPerspectiveCreation), and the internal marketplace was defined as a [catalogue](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CatalogueInternalMarketplace). The project has also moved to [free 'consult'](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_ConsultTermFreed) from reserved status and enforce a [pitch-language rule](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_CreatePerspectiveNotTrain) against the word 'train.' More recently, the naming of the core intelligence moved from AGI to [Synthesizer (SII)](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_SynthesizerNamingRationale), emphasizing human-guided agency. Alongside these decisions, a dense layer of [brand stylization](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_BrandNameStylization) governs the use of backticked tool names, lowercase brand references, and arrow operators to maintain a consistent, code-adjacent identity.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CatalogueInternalMarketplace> ;
